pxctl license activate saas --key 'dafafada'

get cursor to help. But hey, on a reinstall, it's likely the partitions are already tagged, which may interfere. Ideallly I should create a machineconfig for cleanup for next time. Cursor recommended to run those commands:
Command	Purpose	Risk
mdadm --stop /dev/md127	Deactivates the stale RAID array	None (not in use)
wipefs -a /dev/nvme0n1p5	Removes old XFS/KVDB signatures	None (your partition, not OS)
wipefs -a /dev/nvme0n1p6	Removes any signatures	None (already clean)
wipefs -a /dev/nvme0n1p7	Removes RAID member signature	None (your partition)
mdadm --zero-superblock	Clears RAID metadata	None (cleanup only)

